HEADWORD: Medicable
<hw>Med"i*ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>medicabilis</ets>, from <ets>medicare</ets>, <ets>medicari</ets>,
to heal, fr. <ets>medicus</ets> physician. See <er>Medical</er>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being medicated; admitting of being cured or
healed.</def>⟦br⟧
